      <p>
        Use logical equivalence to rewrite the sentence:
        “If wanting peace is wrong, I do not want to be right.”
      </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
      <p>
        If I want to be right, then wanting peace is not wrong.
      </p>
    </solution>
  </question>

